description.narrative: The development objective of the National Agricultural Technology Project for Bangladesh is to effectiveness of the national agricultural technology system. The restructuring will involve a reallocation of the proceeds of the financing and a change in the disbursement category and in the percentage of expenditures to be financed. It will also include minor changes in the definitions of the term 'Common Interest Group' (CIG), the term 'operating costs', and in the responsibilities of the procurement core team under the institutional arrangements. The credit was effective on March 25, 2008 and its closing date is December 31, 2013. The project suffered from initial slow implementation pace due to unpredictable procedural delays in the effectiveness of the research component and in processing the revision of the original development project proposal in compliance with the financing agreement. Since then, the project has built a solid momentum and has emerged as the flagship program for the agriculture sector. The restructuring consists of a reallocation of the proceeds of the financing, and the addition of a new disbursement. In addition, the restructuring will also involve minor changes in the project institutional arrangements.
